President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key Administration posts. The nominees are J. Christopher Giancarlo for Commissioner of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission, Michael P. O'Rielly for Commissioner of the Federal Communications Commission, and Patrick Pizzella for Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority. 

J. Christopher Giancarlo currently serves as the Executive Vice President at GFI Group. He has previously held positions at Fenics Ltd, Brown Raysman Millstein Felder & Steiner, Giancarlo & Gleiberman, Curtis, Mallet-Prevost, Colt & Mosle, and Mudge, Rose, Guthrie, Alexander & Ferdon. Giancarlo received a B.A. from Skidmore College and a J.D. from Vanderbilt University School of Law.

Michael P. O'Rielly is a Policy Advisor in the Office of the Senate Republican Whip, led by U.S. Senator John Cornyn. He has previously worked for U.S. Senator Jon Kyl, the Republican Policy Committee in the U.S. Senate, and the Office of U.S. Senator John Sununu. O'Rielly received a B.A. from the University of Rochester.

Patrick Pizzella is currently the Principal at Patrick Pizzella, LLC. He has previously served as Assistant Secretary of Labor for Administration and Management at the U.S. Department of Labor, worked at Preston Gates Ellis & Rouvelas Meeds LLP, and held positions at the Federal Housing Finance Board, U.S. Department of Education, U.S. Office of Personnel Management, U.S. Small Business Administration, and the U.S. General Services Administration. Pizzella received a B.S. in Business Administration from the University of South Carolina.